
[1]perennial

   PEREN'NIAL, a. [L. perennis; per and annus, a year.]

   1. Lasting or continuing without cessation through the year.

   2. Perpetual; unceasing; never failing.

   3. In botany, continuing more than two years; as a perennial stem or
   root.

   4. Continuing without intermission; as a fever.

    PEREN'NIAL, n. In botany, a plant which lives or continues more than
   two years, whether it retains its leaves or not. That which retains its
      leaves during winter is called an evergreen; that which casts its
                     leaves, deciduous, or a perdifoil.
